caption: Finally visible after years of renovation. Large 18th century wall with sculptures. The fountain itself is quite small

Strange monument, all to the glory of Louis XV; especially since the flow of this fountain, which looks like an imposing although artificial facade, has always been modest. It seems disproportionate given the narrowness of the street and therefore the low setback, which undoubtedly amused Voltaire before he complained about it.

A large monumental fountain, very wide and very high, bearing numerous statues and bas-reliefs but curiously without a basin and whose water outlets are, paradoxically, very small.  It is a curiosity in this street too narrow to accommodate it properly.
Beautiful fountain located next to the Maillol museum, sculpted by Bouchardon and delivered in 1745.
